=== Zeros ===
All formula_107 zeros of formula_3 are real, distinct from each other, and lie in the interval formula_109. Furthermore, if we regard them as dividing the interval formula_110 into formula_111 subintervals, each subinterval will contain exactly one zero of formula_112. This is known as the interlacing property. Because of the parity property it is evident that if formula_113 is a zero of formula_3, so is formula_115. These zeros play an important role in numerical integration based on Gaussian quadrature. The specific quadrature based on the formula_14&#x27;s is known as Gauss-Legendre quadrature.

From this property and the facts that formula_117, it follows that formula_118 has formula_119 local minima and maxima in formula_120. Equivalently, formula_121 has formula_122 zeros in formula_120.

